tp:treatment-sec.p:
Adjective derived from the Sangkulirang Karst formation in Indonesia , where the species occurs (
Rahmadi et al. 2010
).

p.tp:material-citation:
Holotype INDONESIA • ♀ [ovigerous]; East Kalimantan , Gua Ke 4; 01°28′13.23″ N , 117°39′28.14″ E ; Tabalar Ulu District , Berau Regency ;
9 Aug. 2004
; C. Rahmadi leg.; MZB Ambl. 70 [not examined].

tp:treatment-sec.p:
Found in caves in three different limestone hills in the northern part of the Sangkulirang Karst formation, including Tabalar Ulu, a small limestone area with several underground rivers, the Tebo area, where an isolated karst lake is located, and Gua Ampanas (
Rahmadi et al. 2010
).
